
install git,java,maven
$ sudo yum install git -y
$ sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto-devel
vi .bashrc
	export JAVA_HOME='/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-amazon-corretto.x86_64/'
install maven:
# cd /opt
# wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/maven/maven-3/3.9.11/binaries/apache-maven-3.9.11-bin.tar.gz
# tar -xvzf apache-maven-3.9.11-bin.tar.gz
# mv apache-maven-3.9.11 maven
# nano .bashrc
	export M2_HOME='opt/maven'
	export PATH=$PATH:/opt/maven/bin
installing Jenkins:
===================
# wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
# rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
# yum update
# yum install jenkins -y
# sudo systemctl start Jenkins
# cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
outputs a password
=>copy the public ip of Jenkins machine in the browser and open it with 8080 port number
a web page will be opened and let u enter the initialAdminPassword 
paste the password copied 
then=>select plugins to install=>deselect all the plugins=>click install=>
asks to setup username and password
provide the necessary details and click next
in the home page
	goto to manage Jenkins plugins=>availableplugins=>search for git install 5.8.0
                                                        =>select maven integration 3.2.7 then install
go back to Jenkins:
  create a new item =>name it as helloworld webapp, type maven project
  configure the job=>set source code management as git
                     => place the GitHub url of maven project
                     => change the /master to /main
		     => post build actions make it clean install
and then move on to manage Jenkins ->tools->add jdk=>name=>Java=>path of javahome ---/usr/lib/jvm...
                                          ->add git
                                          -> add maven->name=>Maven=>maven home /opt/maven apply and save
before building the application move to jenkins->node->bulitin node->configure
                                                                    =>node properties=>Diskspace monitoring set everything to 0 and click apply and save
then build the job


